post_text:
Technology:
Drive thru device pick up will be from Monday August 3 – 5. Devices will be distributed at Altar Valley Middle School from 8 AM – 2 PM for students registered to attend in the Altar Valley School District for the 2020-2021 school year. AVSD encourages all parents/guardians to pick up a district-owned device for each enrolled student. It will be beneficial for every student to have their own device rather than sharing with family members, we have found that many of the District’s specific learning applications work better on AVSD devices.

District-owned devices come with District purchased security features from Securly. Families will also receive a charging cord, case/sleeve, and personalized information to assist with computer login and use.

You can go to our District website and complete the Technology Work Order form for any technical support at: https://www.altarvalleyschools.org/Technology

post_text: Tomorrow, July 15th, is the last day for drive-up registration. This is registration is for returning students, new students, and open enrollment students. We will be at Altar Valley Middle School for registration K-8 from 8:00 - 12:00. We hope to see you tomorrow!

post_text:
Altar Valley School District K-8 Drive Through Registration for
New and Returning Students at Altar Valley Middle School

Wednesday July 8 & Thursday July 9, 2020

8 am -12 pm

Monday July 13, Tuesday July 14, & Wednesday July 15

8 am -12 pm

Families are asked to stay in their vehicles as staff members will bring out the packets. Follow the signs to the front door of the middle school. There you will be provided your returning student packet or a new student packet. Once you get the packet, you can stay and fill it out in your vehicle or take it home, fill it out and return it on one of the days and times listed above.

AVSD is asking parents to bring:
• Child’s birth certificate
• Parent/guardian’s photo ID
• Child’s immunization records
• Proof of residence
• If new registration a withdrawal form
• A pen

Dear Altar Valley Families:

Due to the recent Executive Order given on Monday June 29 by Governor Ducey we will be making some changes to our summer school program. We will be cancelling in person summer school scheduled July 6 - July 17 and be moving to a Distance Learning Model. The Distance Learning Model will start on Monday July 13 - July 24.

Your child’s summer school teacher will be in contact with you for more details.

post_text:
Dear Altar Valley Families,

As you are aware, Governor Ducey and Superintendent Hoffman announced a statewide closure of all schools through Friday, March 27th. Thank you for your patience and support as we navigate through this difficult time. During the closure, Altar Valley School District will be utilizing a curbside meal service for students. We will provide breakfast and lunch at Robles Elementary from 7:30 – 9 a.m. and 11:30 am -1:00 p.m. starting Monday, March 23rd. Meals are available to all children 18 years old and younger. Children must be present to receive a meal. There will be no adult meals served.

Sincerely,

Dr. Dave Dumon

post_text:
IT WAS A BIG DAY — WE WENT ALL THE WAY TO THE BORDER IN 2020!.

121 VOLUNTEERS CLEANED 250 BAGS OF TRASH FROM 44 MILES OF HIGHWAY. THIS IS AN INCREDIBLE FEAT AND A TRIBUTE TO EVERYONE WHO PARTICIPATED.

Sincere thanks go out to all but especially:

Kyle Thompson, Sarah King and Julia Sitting without whom we could not have done it.

And to Trico Electric Cooperative, Tucson Recycling and Waste Service, Arizona Department of Transportation, Buenos Aires NWR, the Robles Ranch Community Center and AVCA.

Our rock stars this year were Altar Valley Middle School with 26 bags of trash from their adopted miles and
the Tucson Station Explorers with 16 bags.

post_text: Before-School Clubs are starting at AVMS on 10/23! Students received registration forms today. Clubs meet from 7:15-8:15 in the mornings. The forms your student received today have all the details. There will be Wright flight (students go Ryan's Airfield at the end of the program and get to fly), Art Club, Open Gym, and Guitar club. Space is limited please complete your forms and return as soon as possible.

post_text: Thursday Altar Valley traveled down to Calabasas for the 3rd and 4th place matchup. Calabasas came out strong the first game and took game 1. Altar Valley fought back in game 2 and took it to extra points but was unable to close it out. The volleyball team end their season with 4th place in the league tournament. Nice season Eagles! CONGRATULATIONS ALL-STARS!
